{"id": "EUVD-2025-32035", "enisaUuid": "f4b698a5-4a04-3a41-b251-853715eee4c8", "description": "In the Linux kernel, the following vulnerability has been resolved:\n\ndrm/amdgpu: Fix size validation for non-exclusive domains (v4)\n\nFix amdgpu_bo_validate_size() to check whether the TTM domain manager for the\nrequested memory exists, else we get a kernel oops when dereferencing \"man\".\n\nv2: Make the patch standalone, i.e. not dependent on local patches.\nv3: Preserve old behaviour and just check that the manager pointer is not\n    NULL.\nv4: Complain if GTT domain requested and it is uninitialized--most likely a\n    bug.", "datePublished": "2025-10-07T15:19:19", "dateUpdated": "2025-12-20T08:50:56", "baseScore": 0.0, "references": ["https://nvd.nist.gov/vuln/detail/CVE-2022-50527", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/7554886daa31eacc8e7fac9e15bbce67d10b8f1f", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/80546eef216854a7bd47e39e828f04b406c00599", "https://git.kernel.org/stable/c/8ba7c55e112f4ffd2a95b99be1cb1c891ef08ba1"], "aliases": ["CVE-2022-50527", "GHSA-crpq-gx68-2jwq"], "assigner": "Linux", "epss": 0.02, "enisaIdProduct": [{"id": "11f9030c-8f4b-324f-954c-a6306cdb3370", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <8ba7c55e112f4ffd2a95b99be1cb1c891ef08ba1"}, {"id": "2846a7f7-5053-3276-b792-e3b3e9f6df5d", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "4.2"}, {"id": "344e28be-6f7e-31ab-b22a-b34c8a8dd8fa", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <80546eef216854a7bd47e39e828f04b406c00599"}, {"id": "3797e56e-63a4-342a-b832-20dc7de2308b", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "1da177e4c3f41524e886b7f1b8a0c1fc7321cac2 <7554886daa31eacc8e7fac9e15bbce67d10b8f1f"}, {"id": "461e535d-49bb-3c01-ac87-3e65bb4cf33c", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patch: 6.2"}, {"id": "4c958f21-b521-3103-9793-169c2e59afb5", "product": {"name": "Linux"}, "product_version": "patc